Movie: Joan of Arc at the Stake

Review: In 1924, Ida Rubinstein asked Prokofiev to write music for a play about the Jewish heroine of the Book of Judith, a text excluded from the Hebrew canon. Prokofiev stated in his diary that according to Rubinstein, a Belgian director attached to the project "possessed a quality of suffering only a Jew can know, rather than a Frenchman." Only Prokofiev, added Rubinstein, "would be capable of composing sufficiently profound music." To which Prokofiev wisecracked: "Conclusion -I must be the only Jewish composer!"
